CHALLENGE_IDENTIFY_VERIFICATION.learnMoreReceiveTextHeader: How do I confirm my identity by text?
CHALLENGE_IDENTIFY_VERIFICATION.learnMoreReceiveTextMessage: We will send you a one-time code by text to your phone. You'll be prompted to add this code so we can confirm it's really you. Remember: You should never share this code with anyone.
CHALLENGE_IDENTIFY_VERIFICATION.learnMoreReceiveCallHeader: How do I confirm my identity by call?
CHALLENGE_IDENTIFY_VERIFICATION.learnMoreReceiveCallMessage: If you choose to call us or request a call from us, we will provide you with a one-time code. You'll be prompted to add this code so we can confirm it's really you. Remember: You should never share this code with anyone.
CHALLENGE_IDENTIFY_VERIFICATION.learnMoreDriversLicenseHeader: How do I confirm my identity using my driver's license?
CHALLENGE_IDENTIFY_VERIFICATION.learnMoreDriversLicenseMessage: You can take a photo of your driver's license and send to us. We'll use this to confirm it's really you. Remember: You need to give Chase permission to access your camera.
CHALLENGE_IDENTIFY_VERIFICATION.learnMoreVerificationCodeHeader: Why do I need a Chase notification or a one-time code?
CHALLENGE_IDENTIFY_VERIFICATION.learnMoreVerificationCodeMessage:
To keep your accounts secure, we want to make sure it's really you. We'll either send you a notification via the Chase Mobile® app or a one-time code by phone, email or text. Or you can call us to get one. You'll need this notification or code to confirm your identity so you can continue banking.

Remember: You should never share this code with anyone.

If you don't have a Social Security number, we can verify your identity and your accounts based on your date of birth. When you close this screen, choose "Don't have a Social Security number?" and tell us your date of birth.

What if I'm an authorized user on another account?

If you have access to the account, choose "Are you an authorized user on another account?" We'll confirm your identity using your email and security code.

If you're not an authorized user, you'll need to contact the account owner to request online access.

What if I have a Tax Identification number instead?

If you have a Tax Identification number (TIN), we can verify your identity for any business accounts you have. When you close this screen, tell us your TIN to continue.

LOGON_PASSWORD_RESET.customerQuestionsHelpMessage:
What if I don't have a Social Security number?

If you don't have a Social Security number, we can verify your identity and your accounts based on your date of birth. When you close this screen, choose "Social Security number" and then choose "Don't have a Social Security number?" Then, tell us your date of birth.

What if I'm not the primary business account holder?

If you have authorized access to the account, choose "Authorized business user" when you close this screen and we'll verify your identity.

If you're not an authorized user, you'll need to contact the account owner to request online access.

What if I have a pending application?

You'll have limited access to your online accounts. When you close this screen, choose "Pending application" to continue.

What if I have a Tax Identification number instead?

If you have a Tax Identification number (TIN), we can verify your identity for any business accounts you have. When you close this screen, choose "Tax ID number" to continue.

What if I have more than 1 account?

If you have more than 1 account, you only need to choose 1 of them. You'll see all other available accounts when you sign in using your new username and password.

What is a security code?

If you are an authorized business user, you'll create a security code when you get access to a business account. You should be careful not to share this confidential code, because we use it to identify and authenticate you when you contact us for help by phone, at a branch or at chase.com.

If you don't have a security code, please contact the account owner.


What should I do if I don't have any Chase accounts, but am having issues signing into Credit Journey?

If you only use Credit Journey, please call 1-800-935-9935 for help.

LOGON_IDENTIFICATION.identificationAdvisoryMessage:
Why am I being asked to verify my identity?

We want to make sure you're really you. There are several reasons why we might ask you to confirm your identity:
  • You're on a new device or one you haven't used before
  • You changed browsers or browser settings
  • You cleared cookies
  • You or your internet provider modified or updated your software settings
How do I verify my identity?

You can verify your identity with a one-time code that we send to you, which we'll use to confirm that you're the one signing in to your account. You can receive that code in a text, email or voicemail. You may also be able to get verified by responding to a push notification.

How do I get a one-time code?

We can send your code by text, email, or you can call us to receive a code. To get your code, close this message and choose "Next," then follow the instructions.

How do I get push notifications?

We can send you a push notification to verify your identity. To get push notifications, close this message and choose "Send a push notification to my phone," then follow the instructions. This feature may not be available for all users.

To set up push notifications on your iPhone, go to "Notifications" in the "Settings" folder, choose "Chase," then "Allow notifications." On your Android, go to "Settings," choose "Apps," then "Chase." Next choose "App settings," then "Notifications," followed by "Show notifications."
